                                                                                                                                        "raw":  "Notes on Turning Power"
                                                                                                                                    },
                                                                                                                          "author":  "Gareth Holt",
                                                                                                                          "pages":  [
                                                                                                                                        "{\"text\":\"I lashed a wheel to the stream and found a strange comfort in its steady pull. The turn never tires. With gears and a shaft, the motion climbs the stairs to the loft.\"}",
                                                                                                                                        "{\"text\":\"If I can store this rotation, I can drive a press and grind grain without a mule. Call it rotational force. It feels like a secret the river has been keeping.\"}"
